WorkItem.Summary: Bug: PHP Fatal error:  Call to a member function setValue() on a non-object in /PHPExcel/Calculation/FormulaParser.php on line 519

Comments.Message: This error was generated when saving in Excel2007 format.  Saving in Excel5 format did not yield the error.

This error was caused by a formula with mismatched brackets:

  =100*A3/A5)

The second bracket caused a stack underflow.  It would have been nice to have been warned, though, rather than just have it die on me.
